#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:23
#: a47d403257bc4ffcad4088b8fd0c6aad
msgid "Security updates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:26
#: 8d15f451277444e6aaefba5c35c1a7bc
msgid ""
"Security updates are an extremely important part of keeping your Qubes "
"installation secure. When there is an important security incident, we "
"will issue a `Qubes Security Bulletin (QSB) <https://www.qubes-"
"os.org/security/qsb/>`__ via the `Qubes Security Pack (qubes-secpack) "
"<https://www.qubes-os.org/security/pack/>`__. It is very important to "
"read each new QSB and follow any user instructions it contains. Most of "
"the time, simply updating your system normally, as described below, will "
"be sufficient to obtain security updates. However, in some cases, special"
" action may be required on your part, which will be explained in the QSB."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:29
#: 5d6fcce47f6b44cbb19c9955637658cb
msgid "Checking for updates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:32
#: 40c288b1b4874d18ba102c0a46733dac
msgid ""
"By default, the **Qubes Update** tool will appear as an icon in the "
"Notification Area when updates are available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:34
#: d28edd0bb5dc4ba3bf603d9b4c4f42fd
msgid "|Qube Updates Available|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:214
#: 370aa224133144b6a16097ae3feaf2a9
msgid "Qube Updates Available"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:36
#: 7641b8bb59bd4617a6e35580dcc9762d
msgid ""
"However, you can also start the tool manually by selecting it in the "
"Applications Menu under “Qubes Tools.” Even if no updates have been "
"detected, you can use this tool to check for updates manually at any time"
" by selecting all desired items from the list and clicking “Update”."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:40
#: 4c20c246f98e47a29fcb21492e58e763
msgid ""
"For information about how templates download updates, please see "
":ref:`Why don’t templates have normal network access? <user/how-to-guides"
"/how-to-install-software:why don't templates have normal network "
"access?>`       and the :ref:`Updates proxy <user/how-to-guides/how-to-"
"install-software:updates proxy>`      ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:42
#: cf8069b4f2184c4486e2789d1c7d8dce
msgid ""
"By default, most qubes that are connected to the internet will "
"periodically check for updates for their parent templates. You can check "
"the date of the last update check in the “last checked” column. If "
"updates are available for any qube, you will receive a notification as "
"described above, and in the “Updates available” column you will see “YES”"
" for that qube(s). If the update check did not find any new updates, “NO”"
" will appear in the column. Respectively, for qubes that are no longer "
"supported, “OBSOLETE” will be displayed. However, if you have any "
"templates that do *not* have any online child qubes, you will *not* "
"receive update notifications for them. By default, after a week, if "
"updates for a given qube have not been checked, the value in the “Updates"
" available” column will be set to “MAYBE”."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:45
#: b7c5bea50ae7407cafd6fc2d946c9a21
msgid "Installing updates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:48
#: edc0a2eef9ec4fd78f7c3d96532dd1a7
msgid ""
"The standard way to install updates is with the **Qubes Update** tool. "
"(However, you can also perform the same action via the `command-line "
"interface <#command-line-interface>`__.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:50
#: 9d09e94cdde2411ab8fb5677f2cec904
msgid "|Qubes Update|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:217
#: 90330522b17c49b89853ef3c443dbf09
msgid "Qubes Update"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:52
#: 26e0da5d1b7d4780bbae701972446cc3
msgid ""
"You can easily decide which qubes to update by clicking on the checkbox "
"in the column header. At startup, only the qubes for which updates are "
"known are selected for updating, but clicking on the mentioned checkbox "
"will also select all qubes with the “MAYBE” status. It is recommended to "
"update all qubes with the statuses “YES” and “MAYBE”."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:54
#: ff3faa4a4ac241a381d88cb3179bde98
msgid ""
"Then simply follow the on-screen instructions, and the tool will download"
" and install all available updates for you. Note that if you are "
"downloading updates over Tor (``sys-whonix``), this can take a very long "
"time, especially if there are a lot of updates available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:57
#: 6c91cc93ae1c4299b40c691cf43aa562
msgid "Restarting after updating"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:60
#: dbe9226f268d400e9a420fbd465fede6
msgid ""
"Certain updates require certain components to be restarted in order for "
"the updates to take effect:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:62
#: 2c006d476da447e1a760a77162855c49
msgid ""
"QSBs may instruct you to restart certain components after installing "
"updates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:64
#: b2b103ac094e404ab06d537f5c856f04
msgid "Dom0 should be restarted after all **Xen** and **kernel** updates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:66
#: ac65bda9532247178a5d513313b433ad
msgid ""
"On Intel systems, dom0 should be restarted after all ``microcode_ctl`` "
"updates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:68
#: 2eea9e823bd24ca08513fe3400a3a885
msgid ""
"On AMD systems, dom0 should be restarted after all ``linux-firmware`` "
"updates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:70
#: 444ffedc97dc491b8757cad9c008bbd8
msgid ""
"After updating a template, first shut down the template, then restart all"
" running qubes based on that template. The updater will try to do this "
"for you automatically in the last step of updating. Remember to save all "
"your data before restarting!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:75
#: af66edaf0f53452098fbb68e5c056faa
msgid "AEM resealing after updating"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:78
#: 7c2a27800d8a4b488ed4b5eb025794b7
msgid ""
"If you use :doc:`Anti Evil Maid (AEM) </user/security-in-qubes/anti-evil-"
"maid>`, you’ll have to “reseal” after certain updates. It’s common for "
"QSBs to contain instructions to this effect. See the relevant QSB and the"
" `AEM README <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-"
"antievilmaid/blob/main/README>`__ for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-update.rst:81
